article.headline: Cincinnati 63, Oregon State 58
article.story:
CORVALLIS, Ore (AP) -- Treasure Humphries had 22 points and five
steals to lead Cincinnati to a 63-58 overtime win at Oregon State
on Thursday.

Anne Stephens added 17 points and 11 rebounds for the Bearcats
(10-1).

Kim Butler had 21 points and 10 rebounds for Oregon State (6-4).

Humphries had 18 points in the second half and overtime,
including the first five points of the five-minute extra period.
Oregon State got no closer than three the rest of the way.

Cincinnati had just two leads in regulation, 2-0 and 25-24, and
erased a six-point deficit in the final three minutes. Humphries
made a 3-pointer with 1:10 remaining, the final points before the
extra period.

Oregon State missed twice in the last 10 seconds of regulation.

Cincinnati, which won its ninth straight, took the momentum in
overtime with Humphries' 3-pointer and another outside jumper.
